nclose which you are free to use.\r\n\r\n'),(1064,209,'_intro','field_57ebd1b41c03b'),(1065,209,'sub_text','We can take action against unwanted packaging by returning our empty packaging to the manufacturers and even the supermarkets. I am developing a habit of returning or posting empty re-usable packaging to manufacturers with the letter included below; please feel free to use it as a template.\r\n\r\n- The more important a role a employee holds within a company the more impact you will make so if you have the time do some research before hand. Keep in mind the fact that most people understand the need for a more sustainable environment and even the biggest corporations have employees with heart.\r\n\r\n- Used the cheapest postal service, this shouldn\'t cost you too much and there is no rush for delivery.\r\n\r\n- Encourage your friends and family to be part of this change. If they don\'t want to return their packaging they can simply write emails or letters to companies.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/letter-template.pdf\">letter-template</a>'),(1066,209,'_sub_text','field_57e90fea19072'),(1067,206,'hero_image','header-returns.jpeg'),(1068,206,'_hero_image','field_57d2bacfc7bdd'),(1069,206,'intro','I am developing a habit of returning or posting empty re-usable packaging back to the manufacturers to encourage them to consider re-usable options or to make it easier for us return empty packaging for re-use.  I have included a letter template which you are free to use.\r\n\r\n'),(1070,206,'_intro','field_57ebd1b41c03b'),(1071,206,'sub_text',''),(1072,206,'_sub_text','field_57e90fea19072'),(1074,210,'hero_image','header-returns.jpeg'),(1075,210,'_hero_image','field_57d2bacfc7bdd'),(1076,210,'intro','I am developing a habit of returning or posting empty re-usable packaging to manufacturers to encourage them to consider re-fillable options or to make it easier for us return empty packaging for re-use.  I have included a let