sed','closed','','103-revision-v1','','','2016-10-13 13:52:51','2016-10-13 13:52:51','',103,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/103-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(131,1,'2016-10-14 14:26:31','2016-10-14 14:26:31','<p class=\"p1\"><strong>I have been consuming a vegan diet¬†for the past year. I made the decision for ethical reasons due to my concerns with animal mistreatment and the strain that animal based diets places on the environment.</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Initially this was a relaxed decision, however as the year has gone on I have found myself informing friends and family of my dietary requirements and expecting them to cater for me when I visit.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">During this year it has been a learning experience to understand how to meet my body‚Äôs nutritional requirements without meat sources. I found I needed many exotic ingredients that could not be sourced locally. When faced with the fact that they could be causing a bigger carbon footprint than a locally sourced diet incorporating meat, I was resistant. I had become identified with being a vegan.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">It is certainly not a black and white subject and rather than being vegan we should be eating¬†consciously<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">,¬†</span>otherwise there is a danger of identifying with these choices and not being open to new information or different opinions. I will no longer expect people to cater for my personal choice. When I am preparing and choosing food¬†I will go vegan where possible, but when with others I will respect their decisions.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">In this world of polarised opinions this is surely the only way to move forward, to give each other respect, to listen<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">¬† </span>and to accept that we may be wrong.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"p3\"><span class=\"s1\">In every truth the opposite is equally true.¬†</span><span class=\"s2\">That is to say, any truth can only be expressed and put into