y.</p>\r\n            <p className=\"intro intro-3\"><span className=\"fa-stack fa-lg\"><i className=\"fa fa-gbp fa-stack-2x\"></i></span><em className=\"pullout-super\">As margarine sales flatten, Butta offers a plant based alternative that not only looks, tastes and behaves like dairy butter but offers all the benefits of plant based oils.</em></p>\r\n            <p>Retail butter compound annual growth rate (CAGR) forecast for 2015-2020 is 0.4% compared with margarine\'s -0.6%.  Butta bridges the gap between the popularity of plant based foods and the resurgence in butter sales.</p>\r\n        </section>\r\n        <parallax image=\"Girl-loves-cow.jpeg\">\r\n            <h2>Vegans are inspired by health, the environment and animal welfare</h2>\r\n        </parallax>\r\n        <section className=\"section-color-blue intro-list\">\r\n            <h2 className=\"\">Who is the target market for Butta</h2>\r\n            <p className=\"intro intro-3\"><span className=\"fa-stack fa-lg\"><i className=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o fa-stack-2x\"></i></span><em className=\"pullout-super \">Millenials (born between 1977 and 2000)</em></p>\r\n            <p><a href=\"https://www.vegansociety.com/whats-new/news/find-out-how-many-vegans-are-great-britain\">A study by Ipsos MORI in 2016</a>reveals that 42% of all vegans in the UK are between the ages of 18 and 34.</p>\r\n            <p><a href=\"http://www.spins.com/plant-based-foods-webinar/\">Spins Plant Based Foods Growth Opportunities in Retail</a> reports that in the US 1 in 10 millenials (born between 1977 and 2000) are vegan and vegetarian.</p>\r\n            <p className=\"intro intro-3\"><span className=\"fa-stack fa-lg\"><i className=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o fa-stack-2x\"></i></span><em className=\"pullout-super \">Living in urban and suburban areas</em></p>\r\n            <p>In the UK 82% of all vegans live in urban and suburban areas and London contains 22% of all vegans.</p>\r\n<p className=\"intro intro-3\"><span className=\"fa-stack fa-lg\"><i className=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o fa-stack-2x\"></i></span><em className=\"pullout-super \">Inspired to make vegan or vegetarian choices because of animal welfare, the environment or health</em></p>\r\n            <p><a href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/global/2016/sep/11/why-so-many-people-are-converting-to-veganism\">The Guardian</a> recently profiled 4 vegans and their motivation for converting to veganism</p>\r\n        </section>\r\n          <section className=\"section-color-red\">\r\n            <h2>What makes Butta healthy?</h2>\r\n            <div className=\"row\">\r\n              <div className=\"col-md-4\">\r\n                <div className=\"promo\">\r\n                  <div className=\"promo-image-wrapper\">\r\n                    <img src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/cocoanut.png\" width=\"138\" height=\"89\" className=\"image-center\" />\r\n                  </div>\r\n                  <h4>Coconut oil (28%)</h4>\r\n                  <p>Coconut oil is <em className=\"pullout \">good for cholesterol</em>, its high Lauric acid content means that its energy is absorbed quickly giving a <em className=\"pullout \">satisfying</em> feeling of fullness. It also has <em className=\"pullout \">antimicrobial</em> properties which fight viruses and bacterial infections.</p>\r\n                </div>\r\n              </div>\r\n              <div className=\"col-md-4\">\r\n                <div className=\"promo\">\r\n                  <div className=\"promo-image-wrapper\">\r\n                    <img src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/canola.png\" height=\"89\" className=\"image-center\" />\r\n                  </div>\r\n                  <h4>Canola oil (26%)</h4>\r\n                  <p>Canola oil has the <em className=\"pullout \">lowest saturated fat</em> content of all plant oils. Its beneficial high mono-unsaturated fat content protects our heart by maintaining good cholesterol levels and it contains both <em className=\"pullout \">omega-3</em> and <em className=\"pullout \">omega-6</em> essential fatty acids.</p>\r\n                </div>\r\n              </div>\r\n              <div className=\"col-md-4\">\r\n                <div className=\"promo\">\r\n                  <div className=\"promo-image-wrapper\">\r\n                    <img src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/cocoa.png\" width=\"138\" height=\"89\" className=\"image-center\" />\r\n                  </div>\r\n                  <h4>Cocoa butter (21%)</h4>\r\n                  <p>Cocoa butter is an excellent source of natural <em className=\"pullout \">anti-oxidants</em>, omega-3 and omega-6 essential fatty acids as well as nutrients that enhance the mood and <em className=\"pullout \">immune system</em>.</p>\r\n                </div>\r\n              </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n          </section>','About Butta','','inherit','closed','closed','','146-revision-v1','','','2017-03-25 08:10:52','2017-03-25 08:10:52','',146,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/146-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(249,1,'2017-05-10 13:53:23','2017-05-10 13:53:23','','Side Panel','','publish','closed','closed','','acf_side-panel','','','2017-05-10 13:54:03','2017-05-10 13:54:03','',0,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/?post_type=acf&#038;p=249',0,'acf','',0),(250,1,'2017-05-10 14:42:54','2017-05-10 14:42:54','<h3>My Mission</h3>\r\n<p>As a yoga teacher I share the traditional teachings of Hatha yoga,\r\nincorporating asanas, pranayama and meditation. I provide students clear\r\nalignment instructions, confrming hands on adjustments and pointings\r\ntowards meditative awareness. Together we create a loving, open space,\r\nwhere all are welcome to explore and experience the natural state.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>My Story</h3>\r\n<p>I have 8 years experience practicing yoga and meditation. I have received teaching from the Iyengar, Sivananda and Bihar Schools in yoga as well as Buddhist and Advaita teaching in Meditation . Two years ago I quit my job in IT and began to deepen my practice, I spent 3 months in India in a variety of retreats including 1 month in the Osho Nisarga ashram and two weeks at Himalayan Iyengar Yoga center practicing Iyengar yoga and meditation in silence. The following September I attended a silent retreat in Monte Sahaja, Portugal practicing self enquiry under the guidance of Mooji Baba. At the beginning of 2017 I decided it was my life\'s purpose to share these teachings and  returned to India to complete a 200 hour TTC at Hatha Yoga World under the guidance of Pakanj Seth.</p>\r\n<p>Currently I am taking every opportunity to teach, I spent 1 week in Africa burn and was teaching a daily drop in class at the Aliens theme camp, It was great experience teaching classes with up to 50 people. I am motivated and empowered on this new chapter of my life and have no idea what the future holds.</p>','Jon Reading','','publish','closed','closed','','jon-reading','','','2017-05-18 12:40:53','2017-05-18 12:40:53','',0,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/?page_id=250',0,'page','',0),(251,1,'2017-05-10 14:42:54','2017-05-10 14:42:54','Jon is happy','Jon Reading','','inherit','closed','closed','','250-revision-v1','','','2017-05-10 14:42:54','2017-05-10 14:42:54','',250,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/250-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(252,1,'2017-05-18 12:37:06','2017-05-18 12:37:06','<h3>My Mission</h3>\n<p>As a yoga teacher I share the traditional teachings of Hatha yoga,\nincorporating asanas, pranayama and meditation. I provide students clear\nalignment instructions, confrming hands on adjustments and pointings\ntowards meditative awareness. Together we create a loving, open space,\nwhere all are welcome to explore and experience the natural state.</p>\n\n<h3>My Story</h3>\n<p>I have 8 years experience practicing yoga and meditation. I have received teaching from the Iyengar, Sivananda and Bihar Schools in yoga as well as Buddhist